    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\BB\WallTool_02.png">2f7d0004:00000000:2b12bed659b8e838</T>
      <T n="text">0xC3FACA3E<!--String: "Select the Wall Tool and click to begin drawing a wall. Click again to complete the action.\n\nIf you draw an enclosed space with the Wall Tool, it will turn into a room with a floor. You can convert a wall into a room by selecting the wall and dragging the side arrows.\n\nNote: Hit [Esc] to cancel any in progress Build action, such as drawing a wall."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\BB\WallTool_03.png">2f7d0004:00000000:2b12bed659b8e839</T>
      <T n="text">0x75897BAB<!--String: "While using the Wall Tool, you can hold the [shift] key to draw a rectangle instead of a single wall. You can also hold the [ctrl] key to destroy any wall it is drawn over."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\BB\WallTool_04.png">2f7d0004:00000000:2b12bed659b8e83e</T>
      <T n="text">0xE1A1B1AB<!--String: "When drawing walls, you may notice green and yellow highlights.\n\nGreen indicates the wall has passed through architecture that will be modified in some way.\n\nYellow indicates an object that will be moved to the Household Inventory, or sold."--></T>
    </U>
